post_text: The Lancer Booster Club is providing two $500 tuition scholarships - one for a senior boy, one for a senior girl. You must have participated in at least one extra curricular activity during your senior year and provide a one page essay describing how the above activity has impacted your life. In this essay, please also include your post secondary education plans. Please submit to the La Crescent-Hokah High School Guidance Office. The application deadline is April 13th.

post_text:
Today is the DAY!!!! We need your votes Lancer Nation! This levy will not only support our teachers and classrooms, but will also support all of our sports and activities for our students as well. Share this post and make sure that we get to everyone! Even if you don't live in the voting district, you can still share this to make sure that we get to everyone that can vote yes today!

This is the only item on the ballot. All La Crescent precincts will vote at the elementary school gym. All Hokah precincts will vote at the Hokah Community Building (former school). Polls are open 7am to 8pm! We believe in this community. We are LANCER STRONG! LET's Do THIS!!!

Tickets are now available for the 16th Annual Coulee Classic (basketball tournament) at the La Crosse Center on Saturday January 24. Admission for the ENTIRE DAY is $6 (Adult) / $4 (Students). La Crescent game times are:

- Girls 6:30pm vs Onalaska Luther
- Boys 8:00pm vs Onalaska Luther

Please purchase your ticket in advance at La Crescent High School (all home games or in the Activities Office). Revenue from tickets purchased in La Crescent is retained by La Crescent. Below you will find the game schedule for the 14th Annual Coulee Classic on Saturday, January 26 at the La Crosse Center. Come watch La Crescent boys and girls take on G.E.T.

Advance tickets are available for only $5 (Adults) and $3 (Students) and are good for the entire day. Lancer season passes cannot be used for this event.

Purchase your advanced ticket at any boys/girls home basketball game or in the high school activities office (7:30am-4pm). By purchasing your advanced tickets from La Crescent, you are supporting La Crescent activities. If you wait to buy your tickets at the La Crosse Center on the day of the event, you will instead by supporting the Coulee Conference.

9:00 am - West Salem vs. Ona Luther (girls)
10:30 am - West Salem vs. Ona Luther (boys)
12pm - Black River Falls vs. Viroqua (girls)
1:30pm - Viroqua vs. Black River Falls (boys)
3:30pm - La Crescent vs. G-E-T (girls)
5pm - La Crescent vs. G-E-T (boys)
6:30pm - Westby vs. Arcadia (girls)
8pm - Arcadia vs. Westby (boys)

Go to: http://www.couleeconference.org/g5-bin/client.cgi >> Go to Calendar for 1/26/2013

This year La Crescnt is host to the boys Varsity basketball Holiday Tournament.

The first game is Caledonia vs Spring Grove at 6:00 and then La Crescent vs Rushford at 7:30.

Tomorrow the JV boys basketball travel to Caledonia to play Rushford in the first game at 11:15 and their second game is at 1:45 vs Caledonia.

The Varsity girls also start their holiday tournament tomorrow in Spring Grove. Their first game is against Rushford at 6:00.

JV girls basketball team travels to Rushford for 2 games, the first game is at 1:00.

Friday the Varsity boys play their second game of the tournament against Caledonia. Note that the game time has been changed to 6:00 and not 7:30 as originally scheduled.

On Saturday the Varsity girls play their second game against Caledonia at 6:00 in Spring Grove.

Good luck teams!
